<div id="content">
          
		            
            <h1 class="page-title">Chef King</h1>
            <p class="postmetadataw">Posted by: <a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/?author=1" title="Posts by admin" rel="author">admin</a> | on October 12, 2012</p> 
                        
            <div class="content-ver-sep"> </div>
            <div class="entrytext">			<p><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/events-title1.png" ><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-22" title="events title1" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/events-title1.png" alt="" width="222" height="81" /></a></p>
<p>This weekend we are celebrating our love of food!!!!</p>
<p>We are talking about food, we are farming for food, we are sharing recipes, we are creating restaurants in our moon houses, we are playing food word games and MORE!</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/chef-king-festival.png" ><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-159" title="chef king festival" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/chef-king-festival.png" alt="" width="894" height="475" /></a></p>
<p>Got ideas for food games you’d like to play? Send them to the blog before Sunday and maybe our managers will choose your game! Just write ‘Game’ in the subject of your mail, and send your idea, together with your Eko name, to usa_blog@ekoloko.com!</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/style-title1.png" ><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-35" title="style title1" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/style-title1.png" alt="" width="334" height="112" /></a></p>
<p>Look at what fashions we&#8217;ve been cooking up for you! This weekend the style is ‘chef’ – and some of these outfits are smoking hot!</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/chef2.png" ><img class="alignnone  wp-image-162" title="chef2" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/chef2.png" alt="" width="120" height="199" /></a><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/chef3.png" ><img class="alignnone  wp-image-161" title="chef3" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/chef3.png" alt="" width="120" height="215" /></a><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/chef4.png" ><img class="alignnone  wp-image-160" title="chef4" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/chef4.png" alt="" width="122" height="227" /></a></p>
<p>Can&#8217;t wait to see what they&#8217;ll be wearing tomorrow!</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/Recipes-title.png" ><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-109" title="Recipes title" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/Recipes-title.png" alt="" width="274" height="89" /></a></p>
<p>And of course, our blog would not be complete without another great recipe or two! Hope you’re testing these out at home! Perhaps we could create the first ekoloko Chocolate Bean Jim’s cookbook!!! If you like the idea, keep sending in your recipes!!!!!</p>
<p><span style="color: #ff6600;"><strong>Orange and strawberry smoothie </strong><strong>by motimot</strong></span></p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Ingredients:</span></p>
<p>2  cups sliced strawberries.</p>
<p>2  cups low-fat yogurt</p>
<p>½  cup orange juice</p>
<p>½ cup white or brown sugar</p>
<p>½ cup cold water or 7 large ice cubes</p>
<p>1 cardamom pod</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Preparation:</span></p>
<p>Mix all ingredients in a blender. Pour into shake glasses and enjoy!</p>
<p>+-+-+-+-</p>
<p><span style="color: #ff6600;"><strong>Biscuit cake recipe</strong> <strong>by Cchen222</strong></span></p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Ingredients:<a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/picture-of-cake.png" ><img class=" wp-image-168 alignright" title="picture of cake" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/picture-of-cake.png" alt="" width="233" height="177" /></a></span></p>
<p>2 packages of sweet (whipping) cream</p>
<p>1 package of Instant vanilla pudding</p>
<p>2 cups of milk, one for whipping and one for dipping</p>
<p>2-3 packages of biscuits</p>
<p>Some marshmallows</p>
<p>And some chocolate syrup</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">How to make:</span></p>
<p>Mix all liquid ingredients in a bowl (pudding, 1 cup of the milk and the whipping cream) until reaching a uniform cream</p>
<p>Then dip the biscuits in rest of milk (gently! No more than three seconds!)</p>
<p>Then arrange the biscuits in a pan (just one line)</p>
<p>Pour a quarter of your cream on everything ..</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Repeat this action several times </span>until you have used up the biscuits and the cream.</p>
<p>After you do all this, you can decorate with marshmallows or chocolate syrup or even graham cracker crumbs!</p>
<p>When you are done, insert the cake in the refrigerator for a few hours.</p>
            </div>
